Gamelin was a member of the **Jacobin Club**, a radical political group during the French Revolution that fiercely supported the ideals of Marat and Robespierre.

The club played a central role in the Reign of Terror, advocating for revolutionary justice and influencing the Revolutionary Tribunal where Gamelin served as a juror.

His membership reflected his extreme loyalty to the revolutionary cause, though it ultimately contributed to his downfall. \boxed{\text{Jacobin Club}}
